De este módulo 4.

4
00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:15.790
Entonces, primero, There was, significa Hubo

5
00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:18.170
There was =  Hubo.

6
00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:26.830
There was a dog digging in my backyard yesterday.

7
00:00:27.440 --> 00:00:31.750
So, There was viene de There is,

8
00:00:32.060 --> 00:00:43.806
There is = Hay / Is: presente 
There was = Hubo / Was: pasado

9
00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:54.190
PRESENTE = THERE IS a dog digging in my backyard now.
PASADO = THERE WAS a dog digging in my backyard now.

10
00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:59.770
Ahora, cuando vamos a hablar de varias personas o cosas, vamos a hacer (casi lo mismo)

11
00:00:59.780 --> 00:01:05.825
ESTO ES PARA VARIAS PERSONAS/COSAS
There are = Hay
There were = Hubo

12
00:01:05.840 --> 00:01:18.330
PRESENTE: THERE ARE many people in the park playing
Hay muchas personas en el parque jugando.

13
00:01:18.340 --> 00:01:25.250
PASADO: THERE WERE many people in the park
Hubo muchas personas jugando en el parque ayer.

14
00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:31.170
PRESENTE
Para 1 persona: There is
Para varias: There are

15
00:01:31.180 --> 00:01:35.570
PASADO
Para 1 persona: There was
Para varias: There were

16
00:01:35.580 --> 00:01:37.390
Siguiente, quiero que prestes mucha

17
00:01:37.400 --> 00:01:41.910
atención a los verbos, a los verbos de
las acciones que tenemos en la historia,

18
00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:45.870
que están en el pasado, para que tú lo
vas a practicar y te lo vas aprendiendo.

19
00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:52.900
Por ejemplo: (Presente)Get (Pasado) Got
Te voy a decir algunos más.

20
00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:58.650
PASADO: He was / I was 
PRESENTE: He is / I am

21
00:01:58.700 --> 00:02:03.149
Fell = Cayó
Thought = Pensó
Worried = Preocupado

22
00:02:03.200 --> 00:02:15.430
Worried = Preocupó
Started = Comenzó
Went = Fue

23
00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:18.300
Entonces "was" ya lo hemos visto.

24
00:02:18.420 --> 00:02:23.210
Recuerda que lo utilizamos también para
decir que alguien estaba haciendo algo.

25
00:02:23.200 --> 00:02:36.400
For example: "Sonia was dealing with a lot of personal trouble"
Sonia estaba lidiando con muchos problemas personales

26
00:02:36.400 --> 00:02:46.000
Ahora, cuando son varias personas usamos "were" en vez de "was"

27
00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:48.458
"were" significa estaban, for example

28
00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:57.316
1. They were working very hard
2. They were always good friends at high school

29
00:02:57.326 --> 00:03:02.870
Was = Estaba (para 1 persona)
Were = Estaban (para varias personas)

